    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "this seems pretty similar to what you do when making a url, but instead you'd save it to localStorage, much like done at the Yarn site [here](https://github.com/algolia/yarnpkg-website/blob/use-instantsearch-react/js/src/lib/Search/withUrlSync.js#L40). To read out of it is pretty much the same, that's just setting the initial state (like [this](https://github.com/algolia/yarnpkg-website/blob/use-instantsearch-react/js/src/lib/Search/withUrlSync.js#L27)), but replace the url logic with localStorage logic. I think this should be a decision you make as a developer of a site, not as part of the library, what do you think of that? ",
